1076B 101st Legislative Session 1076
2026 South Dakota Legislature
House Bill 1076
AMENDME NT 1076B
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Representative Gosch
1 An Act to revise restrictions on residence within a community safety zone and to
2 declare an emergency.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That § 22-24B-23 be AMENDED:
5 22-24B-23. No person who is required to register as a sex offender pursuant to
6 this chapter may establish a residence or reside within a community safety zone unless:
7 (1) The person is incarcerated in a jail or prison or other correctional placement which
8 is located within a community safety zone;
9 (2) The person is on parole or probation and has been assigned to a halfway house or
10 supervised living center within a community safety zone;
11 (3) The person is homeless and has been admitted to a community homeless shelter
12 within a community safety zone by an appropriate community official;
13 (4) The person is placed in a health care facility licensed pursuant to chapter 34-12,
14 or certified under Title XVIII or XIX of the Social Security Act as amended to
15 December 31, 2001, or receiving services from a community service provider
16 accredited or certified by the Department of Human Services or the Department of
17 Social Services, which is located within a community safety zone;
18 (5) The person was under age eighteen at the time of the offense and the offender
19 was not tried and convicted of the offense as an adult;
20 (6) The person established and inhabited the residence as of:
21 (a) July 1, 2024 2006, if the community safety zone includes a school, public
22 park, public playground, or public pool; or
23 (b) July 1, 2024, if the community safety zone includes a domestic abuse
24 shelter or sexual assault shelter;
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1076B 2 1076
1 (7) The school, public park, public pool, domestic abuse shelter, sexual assault shelter,
2 or public playground was built or established subsequent to the person's
3 establishing residence at the location; or
4 (8) The circuit court has entered an order pursuant to § 22-24B-28 exempting the
5 offender from the provisions of §§ 22-24B-22 to 22-24B-28, inclusive.
6 A violation of this section is a Class 6 felony. Any subsequent violation is a Class 5
7 felony.
8 Section 2. Whereas, this Act is necessary for the immediate preservation of the public peace,
9 health, or safety, an emergency is hereby declared to exist, and this Act shall be in full force
10 and effect from and after its passage and approval.
Underscores indicate new language.
